entry.title: [autofill in devtools] Emit filled fields information to devtools.
entry.content:
This CL uses the newly added Observer. We react to a form being filled and in the case where its an address form, the filled_fields info

is sent to devtools.



Regarding the profile and the address used to fill the form:

1. Unfortunately CDP does not allow to have an array of arrays

therefore the current API has to nest objects, see AddressUI.

2. We are using AutofillAddressUIComponent to build the address UI

representation. This is a 2D array, where each inner array will

have a an object of type `AddressField`, this is what devtool will get:



[

[{name: "GIVE_NAME", value: "Bruno"},

{name: "FAMILY_NAME", value: "Braga"}],

[{name: "CITY", value: "Munich"},

{name: "ZIP", value: "81456"}],

]



which it can use to build:



Bruno Braga

Munich 81456



3. Sending address information to devtools is safe because developers do not have access to it AND autofill is under an experimental domain.



Bug: 1451267

entry.title: Avoid crashing when loading the same profile twice
entry.content:
This CL adds debug information in crash keys to help identify the cause

for the double-loading of profiles.



This specifically target the case where one (or more) asynchronous loads

are in flight when a synchronous load is attempted. It should not change

existing behavior, except in scenarios that were crashing.



It logs the call stack of the most recent asynchronous load, as well as

the profile path (if the profile path is different, then the call stack

is not useful and should be ignored).



The crash is converted to DumpWithoutCrashing(), and Chrome now

waits until the asynchronous load finishes, by actively spinning the

run loop. This is only a workaround.



Cleaner fixes could be:

- remove the synchronous load from the startup code, and use only the

asynchronous API. This is not easy to do, because the profile is

currently loaded very early in the startup, at a time where the message

loop is not started yet.

- Change the asynchronous callers to wait until a later point in the

startup sequence, to avoid conflicting with the initial synchronous

load. Hopefully this CL will allow identifying these callers.

To make PA_BASE_*CHECK() inside PartitionAlloc, make PA_BASE_*CHECK()

on-stack objects. This requires more stack size.

buffer size for logging 256u. (1024u causes the test's failure on

includes logging.h, we will see "error: 'PA_LOG' macro redefined",

because chromeos/ash/components/multidevice/logging/logging.h

defines PA_LOG(). So split logging.h into logging.h and log_message.h,

and make check.h include log_message.h.

entry.title: Report space shortage for non-fitting grid items.
entry.content:
Prior to crrev.com/c/4512177 , we accidentally used the tallest

unbreakable block-size as space shortage for grid containers, when it

broke inside because some item would have to be pushed to a subsequent

column. The CL made sure that we wouldn't mix up space shortage and

tallest unbreakable block-size (those two values share storage in

NGLayoutResult). And with that, the truth was revealed: the grid layout

algorithm doesn't always report space shortage. This could cause the

column layout algorithm to cowardly give up and finish, since it

wouldn't be able to make any further progress, not knowing the column

block-size stretch amount. This would result in creating more columns

than specified.



When we decide that a grid item belongs in a subsequent column, and

we're in column stretch mode (i.e. balancing is enabled, and we're past

the initial balancing pass), lay out the grid item anyway, so that we

can calculate the space shortage.



Bug: 1474979

entry.title: Prerender: Disallow prerendering view-source URLs
entry.content:
This CL disallows view-source URLs on embedder initiated prerendering.

Before this CL, PrerenderNavigationThrottle checked if prerendering

URLs have http(s) scheme, but this did not work for view-source URLs

like "view-source:https://www.example.com/prerendering" because the

throttle uses NavigationRequest::GetURL() for the check that returns a

URL without the "view-source:" prefix.



After this CL, PrerenderHostRegistry::CreateAndStartHost() checks scheme

of the prerendering URLs that may include the "view-source:" prefix.

Also PrerenderNavigationThrottle still checks the scheme for redirection

case.



For speculation rules, ParseSpeculationRule() in Blink rejects

non-http(s) URLs. This change does not affect the behavior.

entry.title: [Promise Icons] Suppress promise app creation for default ARC apps
entry.content:
Default ARC apps have icons in the Launcher and Shelf before they are

actually installed on the device. This means that when the default ARC

apps do start installing, it will trigger the creation of a promise app

which will show in the Launcher/ Shelf, causing duplicate icons for the

same app. To avoid these duplicates, suppress the creation of the

promise app when the package ID matches with an app already registered

in AppRegistryCache.



In the future, the default ARC apps in the Launcher/ Shelf will be

refactored to use the Promise App Service to avoid these conflicts.

entry.title: Introduce per browsing context group page pauser
entry.content:
Existing ScopedPagePauser pauses all pages. This behavior can be

problematic when a renderer process hosts two same origin tabs

with different browsing context groups: If one tab pauses pages, the

pages belong to the other tab are also paused unexpectedly.



To avoid such situation, this CL introduces a page pauser that only

pauses pages that belong to the given browsing context group. The new

pauser is behind a flag and the flag is disabled by default, as we

also need to update other components such as scheduler so that these

are aware of per browsing context group pauser.



Bug: 1475531

entry.title: Fix Non-SharedBuffer Cardboard Rendering
entry.content:
When testing with WebXR SharedBuffers disabled, the Cardboard image

was inverted. It was discovered that the inversion that we need to apply

for shared buffer mode was not needed for the non-shared buffer mode.*



*There is a slight chance that this is mainly a coincidence, since we

are also ignoring the transform that XrImageTransportBase::

OnFrameAvailable passes in to us, because we don't really have a good

place to copy it without performing an additional texture copy, as

experimentation revealed that using the transform calculated from the

previous frame in CopyMailboxToSurfaceAndSwap also seemed to resolve the

issue.

entry.title: Fix alignment for IDR_THEME_TOOLBAR and IDR_THEME_FRAME.
entry.content:
This CL makes two changes:



(1) It standardizes the logic from different views for painting the

toolbar theme, tab theme, and frame theme. This ensures that the themes

are painted consistently. The new logic is x-platform. Although it must

be called in several platform-specific classes, the base calculations

can now be shared.



(2) It aligns the origin point for the toolbar theme, tab theme, and

frame theme. This fixes some themes (which relies on this behavior) and

breaks some themes (which rely on the behavior that the toolbar theme is

aligned with the top painted pixel of the active tab). I made this

choice for two reasons:



(2a) This matches the pre-existing code level documentation. (2b) The

themes that this breaks are generally relying on implementation details

of chrome. For example, some themes rely on the shape of the tabs: flat

upper side. Other themes rely on the exact DIP height of the current tab

strip.



Note that most themes are not affected by (2) since most themes use a

repeating pixel for IDR_THEME_TOOLBAR.
